# ========================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ========================================

# Environment Variable Security:
# - Never commit .env.local to version control
# - Use different tokens for development and production
# - Rotate API keys regularly
# - Monitor API usage for unusual activity
# - GitHub tokens should have minimal required permissions

# Privacy Implementation:
# - All error logging is server-side only with PII sanitization
# - No client-side tracking or user identification
# - Rate limiting protects APIs without user tracking
# - CSP headers prevent XSS attacks
# - No third-party monitoring services that collect user data

# Production Security:
# - NODE_ENV=production enables security features
# - Rate limiting: 100 requests per minute per IP
# - Error logs sanitize sensitive information
# - No browser-side error tracking

# ========================================
# API RATE LIMITS & QUOTAS
# ========================================

# GitHub API:
# - Personal token: 5,000 requests/hour
# - Public data: Lower rate limits
# - Monitor usage: https://api.github.com/rate_limit

# Semantic Scholar API:
# - Free tier: 1 request per second
# - Higher limits available with API key
# - Check limits: https://api.semanticscholar.org/

# Vercel Analytics:
# - No request limits (privacy-first)
# - Data retention: 24 hours
# - No user-level data collected
# - Automatic with @vercel/analytics package

# ========================================
# DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOW
# ========================================

# First-time setup:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Fill in GITHUB_TOKEN and GITHUB_USERNAME (required)
# 3. Add optional integrations as needed
# 4. Run: npm run prebuild (extracts colors from images)
# 5. Run: npm run dev

# Production deployment:
# 1. Set NODE_ENV=production
# 2. Verify all required variables are set
# 3. Test build: npm run build
# 4. Deploy with platform-specific environment variables

